28. prasinae iacticni: according to Dio, lix. 14, this was Gaius' favorite party. The drivers of the different chariots were distinguished by the color oi their garments. Hence, from the zeal with which different people espoused the cause oi the different colors, there arose four parties or factione, named respectively, sectio albula (white), prasino (green), rosata (red), and corteto (blue). When Domitian instituted the practice oi starting six, instead of four, chariots at once, two new factione were added, sectio curata (golden) and purpura (purple), but these were not long kept up. There were frequent riots and encounters between these various sections, the worst oi which occurred at Constantinople in 532 sm. (the Nice rebellion), in which thirty thousand are said to have perished.
